1************
 * UT485    *
 ************
01. PURPOSE
 ----------
0   UT485 WAS WRITTEN TO SUPPLY A SIMPLE METHOD OF UPDATING
    FILES (WITH KEY FIELDS) AT THE RECORD LEVEL. UPDATE
    RECORDS ARE AUTOMATICALLY SORTED INTO THE CORRECT SEQUENCE
    AND MERGED WITH THE EXISTING MASTER TO ALLOW ADDITIONS,
    DELETIONS AND MODIFICATIONS. OPTIONALLY, A USER EXIT MAY
    BE INVOKED, WHEN MATCHING UPDATE AND MASTER KEYS ARE FOUND,
    TO GIVE AN UPDATING FACILITY AT THE FIELD LEVEL AND TO ALLOW
    OTHER USER FUNCTIONS.
02. LIMITATIONS
 --------------
0   1. ONLY SEQUENTIAL DATA SETS MAY BE PROCESSED.
    2. BECAUSE THE PROGRAM DYNAMICALLY INVOKES THE
       SORT/MERGE, CERTAIN SORT/MERGE DD STATEMENTS
       (LISTED LATER) ARE MANDATORY.
    3. ONLY FIXED LENGTH RECORDS MAY BE PROCESSED.
    4. A MAXIMUM OF TEN CONTROL FIELDS FOR SORT/MERGE
       MAY BE PROCESSED.
    5. THE RECORD LAYOUTS OF BOTH UPDATE AND MASTER RECORDS
       ARE ASSUMED TO BE IDENTICAL.
    6. ALL KEY FIELDS ARE ASSUMED TO BE 'CH' FORMAT.
03. INPUT DATA
 -------------
0   1. PARM OF EXEC STATEMENT
 ----------------------------
0      A.     KEYS=(PPPP,1111,........)                              (MANDATORY)
              THIS MANDATORY KEYWORD PARAMETER DEFINES THE CONTROL
              FIELDS FOR SORT/MERGE. A MAXIMUM OF TEN DIFFERENT
              CONTROL FIELDS MAY BE USED.
              PPPP  IS ONE TO FOUR NUMERIC DIGITS DEFINING THE
                    LEFT MOST POSITION OF THE FIELD IN THE RECORD.
              1111  IS ONE TO FOUR NUMERIC DIGITS DEFINING THE
                    LENGTH OF PRECEDING POSITION FIELD.
1************
 * UT485    *
 ************
